    "With little to no involvement of central entities, it can become unclear who should be held accountable for potential wrongdoings on a decentralized financial ecosystem.",
    "\", p.6 3 Chen and Bellavitis [78] Flawed oracle (Oracle distrust) \"[D]ecentralized platforms are more likely to achieve distributed trust on inputs that can be objectively recorded and verified."
